## Part 1 — Transcription pipeline upgrade

### Word-level timestamps

The existing Whisper integration in `transcription-worker.ts` currently uses `return_timestamps: true`, which returns segment-level timestamps only. Both subtitle templates require word-level timestamps.

**Change `return_timestamps: true` to `return_timestamps: 'word'` in `transcription-worker.ts`.**

The result object will then include both segment-level and word-level data. Update `transcription.ts` to surface word timestamps in the result. The existing Transcribe tab must continue to work unchanged — word timestamps are additive to the existing output, not a replacement.

**Updated data shape from transcription:**

```typescript
interface WordTimestamp {
  word: string;
  start: number;  // seconds
  end: number;    // seconds
}

interface SubtitleSegment {
  start: number;
  end: number;
  text: string;
  words: WordTimestamp[];  // word-level timestamps within this segment
}
```

**Performance note:** Word-level timestamps increase transcription time, particularly on low-end Android devices. The agent must ensure the existing progress messaging in the transcription UI is clear enough that users do not interpret a longer run as a hang. No additional UI work required beyond confirming this.

