## Part 2 — Shared subtitle engine

### New file: `src/lib/utils/subtitles.ts`

This is the core module. It must import nothing from audiogram-specific files (`AudiogramPage.svelte`, `CompositionCanvas.svelte`, `compositor.ts`, `stores.ts`). It accepts and returns plain data only. This is the architectural guarantee that makes future extraction to a standalone app clean.

### Style model

```typescript
type SubtitleTemplate = 'flow' | 'focus';
type FontSize = 'small' | 'medium' | 'large';
type MaxLines = 1 | 2;

interface SubtitleStyle {
  template: SubtitleTemplate;
  fontSize: FontSize;
  maxLines: MaxLines;
  verticalPosition: number;    // 0–1, proportion from top of canvas
  textColor: string;           // hex, default #FFFFFF
  spotlightEnabled: boolean;
  spotlightColor: string;      // hex, default #FFD700
  outlineEnabled: boolean;
  outlineColor: string;        // hex, default #000000
  shadowEnabled: boolean;
  shadowColor: string;         // hex, default #000000 (at 50% opacity, hardcoded)
}
```

### Template behaviour

**Flow**
Words within the active segment accumulate left-to-right, each fading in individually with a smooth short fade (~150ms). Once a word has fully faded in, it sits at full opacity in the base text colour. The word currently fading in displays in the spotlight colour if spotlight is enabled; once fully visible it reverts to the base text colour and the next word begins fading in. By default: white text, outline on, shadow off, spotlight off.

**Focus**
The full line or lines of the active segment appear together instantly. The word whose timestamp window contains `currentTime` is rendered in the spotlight colour. All other words in the segment render in the base text colour. By default: white text, outline on, shadow off, spotlight on in gold (#FFD700).

### Word-timing within a segment for Focus

Use the `words` array from the upgraded transcription output. At any given `currentTime`, the active word is the entry in `words` where `word.start <= currentTime < word.end`. If `currentTime` falls in a gap between words, the most recently completed word holds the spotlight.

### Word-timing within a segment for Flow

Use the same `words` array. Each word begins its fade-in animation at `word.start`. The fade duration is 150ms. Words that have completed their fade-in (i.e. `currentTime > word.start + 0.15`) render at full opacity in the base text colour. The word currently fading in (`word.start <= currentTime <= word.start + 0.15`) renders in the spotlight colour if spotlight is enabled.

### Text rendering rules

No filled background rectangles behind text in either template.

Font: Inter (already self-hosted). Font sizes map proportionally to canvas height: small = 3.5%, medium = 5%, large = 7%. This ensures correct scaling regardless of export resolution.

**Text wrapping:** `wrapSegmentText(text, charsPerLine, maxLines)` wraps segment text to respect the maxLines ceiling. Two lines is a maximum, not a target. Single-line display is normal for standard speech pace.

**Character budget:** `calculateCharsPerLine(canvasWidth, fontSize)` derives how many characters fit per line from canvas width and font size. This is internal to the engine and not exposed to the UI.

**Outline:** if `outlineEnabled`, apply `ctx.strokeText()` before `ctx.fillText()`. Stroke width 2.5px. Stroke colour is `outlineColor`.

**Shadow:** if `shadowEnabled`, set `ctx.shadowColor` to `shadowColor` at 50% opacity (hardcoded), `ctx.shadowBlur = 4`, `ctx.shadowOffsetX = 1`, `ctx.shadowOffsetY = 1`. Reset shadow after drawing.

**Vertical position:** subtitle block is placed at `canvasHeight * verticalPosition`. Default value positions subtitles in the lower quarter of the canvas.

### Core engine functions

`getActiveSegment(segments, currentTime)` — returns the segment whose start/end window contains currentTime, or null.

`wrapSegmentText(text, charsPerLine, maxLines)` — wraps text respecting maxLines ceiling.

`calculateCharsPerLine(canvasWidth, fontSize)` — internal character budget calculation.

`drawSubtitle(ctx, segment, style, canvasWidth, canvasHeight, currentTime)` — draws the subtitle block for the active segment onto a 2D canvas context. Handles both Flow and Focus rendering. Called from `renderFrame()` in the export pipeline and during live playback preview. `currentTime` is required for both word-fade timing (Flow) and active word detection (Focus).

`mergeSegments(segments, indexA, indexB)` — merges two adjacent segments. Text joined with a space. Words arrays concatenated. Timestamp spans from start of A to end of B.

`splitSegmentAtWord(segment, wordIndex)` — splits a segment at a word boundary using word-level timestamps. First segment spans `segment.start` to `words[wordIndex].end`. Second segment spans `words[wordIndex + 1].start` to `segment.end`. Text and words arrays split accordingly. This is acoustically accurate because it uses real word timestamps.

`reflow(segments, style, canvasWidth, canvasHeight)` — after any text edit or style change, re-wraps all segment text against the current character budget. Timestamps and word arrays are never modified by reflow.

