## Part 3 — Audiogram subtitles

### Integration points

**`src/lib/components/AudiogramPage.svelte`** — add a Subtitles `TogglePanel` following the exact same pattern as Waveform, Title, and Light effect. It renders `SubtitlePanel.svelte`.

**`src/lib/utils/compositor.ts`** — in `renderFrame(currentTime)`, add a call to `drawSubtitle()` from the subtitle engine when subtitles are enabled and `getActiveSegment()` returns a non-null result. Subtitles render as the topmost layer, after all other layers.

**`src/lib/utils/webcodecs-export.ts` and MediaRecorder path** — no changes required. Both paths already route through `renderFrame()`.

### New component: `src/lib/components/SubtitlePanel.svelte`

Collapsible toggle panel containing all subtitle controls. This same component is reused in the video subtitle page.

**Panel contents in order:**

**Template picker** — two buttons: Flow and Focus. Tapping a template immediately updates the canvas preview using placeholder text at the correct size, position and style. Whisper has not run at this point; this is a visual style preview only. Focus is the default.

**Text size** — three-stop slider: Small / Medium / Large. Updates canvas preview immediately.

**Max lines** — toggle: 1 line / 2 lines. Default: 2 lines (as a ceiling). Updates canvas preview immediately.

**Vertical position** — continuous slider. Top of range places subtitles near top of canvas; bottom of range near bottom. Default: lower quarter. Updates canvas preview immediately.

**Style options** — four rows, each following the same pattern:

```
Text      [colour button → opens ColorPicker, default #FFFFFF]
Spotlight [toggle] [colour button → opens ColorPicker, default #FFD700]
Outline   [toggle] [colour button → opens ColorPicker, default #000000]
Shadow    [toggle] [colour button → opens ColorPicker, default #000000]
```

Reuse the existing `ColorPicker.svelte` component exactly as used elsewhere in the app. All option changes update the canvas preview immediately.

**Generate subtitles button** — triggers the Whisper transcription worker via the existing `transcribeAudio()` in `transcription.ts`. On completion, `SubtitleSegment[]` (with word timestamps) is stored in subtitle state. Real subtitles appear on the canvas during playback. The Edit button activates. The Reset button activates.

**Reset subtitles button** — visible and active only after generation. Clears all subtitle state, returns the panel to its pre-generation state, removes subtitles from the canvas. Requires a single confirmation before clearing, to prevent accidental loss.

**Edit subtitles button** — inactive until generation is complete. On tap, opens the edit drawer.

### Edit drawer

A bottom sheet or slide-in drawer consistent with existing AudioFlam UI patterns. Contains a scrollable list of all subtitle segments.

Each segment displays:

- Timestamp range — read-only, e.g. `0.8s – 2.1s`
- Editable text field — user corrects spelling, proper nouns, garbled words. On any edit, `reflow()` runs on that segment immediately.
- A split button (÷) — opens a word-picker within the segment showing each word as a tappable chip. Tapping a word calls `splitSegmentAtWord()` at that word index using real word timestamps. The drawer updates to show the two resulting segments.
- Between each pair of adjacent segments, a merge button (+) — calls `mergeSegments()`. The drawer updates immediately.

**Done button** — closes drawer. If any changes were made, `reflow()` runs across all segments and the canvas preview updates. No re-running Whisper.

