## Part 4 — Video subtitle page

### New tab

Add a tab to the main navigation alongside TTS, Audiogram, and Transcribe. Label: **Subtitle video**.

### New component: `src/lib/components/VideoSubtitlePage.svelte`

Modelled on the audiogram page but simplified. Present: video upload, trim control, title panel (reuse `TitlePanel.svelte` unchanged), subtitle panel (reuse `SubtitlePanel.svelte` unchanged), export button. Absent: image upload, audio upload, waveform panel, light effect panel.

**Upload zone** — single dashed upload area accepting MP4, MOV, WebM. On mobile, triggers device camera roll. Displays a `<video>` preview element once loaded.

**Trim control** — a scrubber below the video preview with two drag handles representing in-point and out-point. Displays the selected clip duration. Trim is applied at export time; it is not destructive on the uploaded file. This is a convenience tool — frame-accurate precision is not required.

**Playback** — play/pause control. During playback, the canvas renders video frames with subtitles burned in via `drawSubtitle()`, serving as the subtitle preview. No separate preview step is needed.

**Subtitle panel** — `SubtitlePanel.svelte` reused exactly. Generate, Reset, Edit all behave identically to the audiogram mode. The audio track is extracted from the uploaded video for Whisper transcription.

**Title panel** — `TitlePanel.svelte` reused exactly.

**Export button** — label: Download video. Routes through the existing `smartExportVideo()` pipeline.

### Canvas rendering for video mode

In `renderFrame(currentTime)`, draw the video frame using `ctx.drawImage(videoElement, 0, 0, canvasWidth, canvasHeight)` after seeking the video element to `currentTime` offset by the trim in-point. Title and subtitle layers draw on top, identically to the audiogram path.

**iOS Safari risk:** `ctx.drawImage()` from a video element has known constraints on iOS. Test this on iOS Safari as the first action in Stage 4. If it fails, the cloud transcode path via api.video is the fallback. Document the finding in AGENTS.md regardless of outcome before proceeding.

