## Build order

Build and commit at the end of each stage:

**Stage 1 — Transcription upgrade**
Amend `transcription-worker.ts` to use `return_timestamps: 'word'`. Update `transcription.ts` result handling. Verify the existing Transcribe tab still works. Commit.

**Stage 2 — Subtitle engine**
Implement `subtitles.ts` in full. Unit test `drawSubtitle()`, `wrapSegmentText()`, `mergeSegments()`, `splitSegmentAtWord()`, `reflow()` in isolation before integration. Commit.

**Stage 3 — Audiogram subtitle panel**
Implement `SubtitlePanel.svelte`. Integrate into `AudiogramPage.svelte` and `compositor.ts`. Full audiogram subtitle flow working end to end: generate, preview on canvas during playback, reset, edit drawer with split and merge. Commit.

**Stage 4 — Video subtitle page**
Implement `VideoSubtitlePage.svelte`. Add new tab. Test iOS `ctx.drawImage()` from video element immediately. Document finding in AGENTS.md. Full video subtitle flow working end to end. Commit.

**Stage 5 — Trim control**
Add trim scrubber to video page. Apply trim offset in `renderFrame()`. Test export with trim applied. Commit.

**Stage 6 — Merge to main**
Ensure all stages are tested. `git checkout main && git merge feature/subtitles`. Push. Update AGENTS.md subtitle section to reflect completed feature.

